- The method `convertToTitleCase` takes a string and converts it to title case.
- It first checks if the input is null or empty and returns it as is.
- It splits the input into words using whitespace.
- The first word is capitalized.
- For each subsequent word, it checks if it is in the exception list. If not, it capitalizes the first letter and adds the rest of the word.
- If it is an exception word, it is added as is.
- The output is printed in the `main` method with the given input string.

